cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper deals with the evaluation of genotypic diversity measurements in evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the need for a validation framework for these measurements, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of diversity requirements involves controlled population arrangements, which could be considered a form of system analysis and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the evaluation of different measurements, which could be seen as a form of data analysis and statistics (cs.DS).
